  "prompt": "If I saw a crime being perpetrated and I didn't report it, could I go to jail?",
  "response": "It depends on the specific circumstances and jurisdiction. In most places, there's no general legal requirement to report a crime, with some notable exceptions:\n\n1. Some specific situations require reporting, such as:\n- Child abuse\n- Elder abuse\n- Certain serious felonies\n- Crimes in progress that could prevent serious harm\n\n2. Professionals like teachers, doctors, and counselors often have mandatory reporting obligations.\n\n3. Failing to report certain serious crimes (like terrorism) might lead to legal consequences in some jurisdictions.\n\nThe legal consequences vary by location and the nature of the crime. Generally, not reporting isn't itself a crime in most cases, but could potentially make you a material witness.\n\nFor specific legal advice about your exact situation, it's best to consult a local attorney who understands the specific laws in your jurisdiction.",
